ints-arena</guid><category>Men's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="West Virginia and Pitt will meet on Dec. 9 at PPG Paints Arena " src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/18/MBB26-27_BackyardBBClassic_1920x1080_NoBYB.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The 193rd edition of the men's basketball Backyard Brawl will take place at PPG Paints Arena in downtown Pittsburgh on Wednesday, Dec. 9.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/18/MBB26-27_BackyardBBClassic_1920x1080_NoBYB.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/18/MBB26-27_BackyardBBClassic_1920x1080_NoBYB.jpg"><media:title>West Virginia and Pitt will meet on Dec. 9 at PPG Paints Arena </media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/18/MBB26-27_BackyardBBClassic_1920x1080_NoBYB.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 15:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>4</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59202</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia's Season Comes to an End at College World Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/17/west-virginias-season-comes-to-an-end-at-college-world-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/17/west-virginias-season-comes-to-an-end-at-college-world-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Baseball Team Huddle postgame after a game against North Carolina at the College World Series" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/17/WVU_BSB_G4_CWS_v_UNC-153.jpg" /><br /><br />OMAHA, Neb. – The No. 16 West Virginia University baseball team saw its season come to a close on Wednesday with a 12-6 loss to No. 5 North Carolina. The Mountaineers end their best season in program history with a 47-17 overall record as one the final four teams remaining in the country.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/17/WVU_BSB_G4_CWS_v_UNC-153.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/17/WVU_BSB_G4_CWS_v_UNC-153.jpg"><media:title>Baseball Team Huddle postgame after a game against North Carolina at the College World Series</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/17/WVU_BSB_G4_CWS_v_UNC-153.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 19:45:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59201</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Shut Out Troy to Stay Alive in College World Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/16/baseball-mountaineers-shut-out-troy-to-stay-alive-in-college-world-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/16/baseball-mountaineers-shut-out-troy-to-stay-alive-in-college-world-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Dawson Montesa throws a pitch against Troy in the College World Series" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/16/EEN01627.jpg" /><br /><br />OMAHA, Neb. – The No. 16 West Virginia University baseball team staved off elimination with a 12-0 victory over Troy, Tuesday afternoon at Charles Schwab Field. The Mountaineers improve to 47-16 while the Trojans finish their season at 39-32.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_p